name: transmission network construction, electricity, high voltage direct current subsea cable | transmission network, electricity, high voltage direct current subsea cable | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/26891/documentation

This dataset represents the production, laying, and decommissioning of 1 km of an high voltage direct current subsea cable transmission network. All materials end up in used cables. The service life of the network was assumed to be 40 years. Maintenance is included as a service. ;;The inventory was modelled according to A. Arvesen et al. (2014) LCA of an offshore grid interconnecting wind farms and customers across the north sea. Int J Life Cylce Assess 19:826-837. p.831, table 2.

The activity starts with cable production according to material composition (energy requirements for cable production not included) and cable laying. Maintenance is included as a service. Substations are not included.

The activity ends with the decommissioning of subsea cable according to material composition.
category: F:Construction/42:Civil engineering/422:Construction of utility projects/4220:Construction of utility projects

processDocumentation.samplingDescription: material composition according to environmental product declaration, further information from literature
